{# Detect a populated `body` field safely.

   `entry.fieldValues` only contains the fields in THIS entry's field layout, so
   `entry.fieldValues.body` is set only when the entry's type actually has a
   `body` field. The `?? false` falls through to the help message when it's
   absent or empty.

   Why not the obvious alternatives:
   - `entry['body'] is defined` renders blank when a `body` field exists
     elsewhere in the project but not on this entry's type (Craft registers
     every field handle globally).
   - `entry.body` (and `entry.body ?? false`) throw a Twig RuntimeError under
     strict_variables (dev mode) when no `body` field exists, because Craft
     routes the lookup through the element's magic __call. `??` does not
     suppress an exception thrown inside __call. (Verified against a live
     Craft 5 install.) #}

{% if entry.fieldValues.body ?? false %}
    {{ entry.body }}
{% else %}
    <p>
        <a href="{{ url('settings/fields/new') }}">Create a field</a> with the handle of <code>body</code>
        <b>or</b>
        use the <a href="{{ url('settings/plugins/usermanual#settings-templateOverride-field') }}">Template Override</a> option to define your own fields.
    </p>
{% endif %}
